Thanks to Trump
I don't wear my Veteran hat
Don't fly the flag
Don't talk to my neighbors
Or daughter
Anymore
I quit my job
Locked in
Hiding
From a virus
I don't see Veterans
Once bonded by oath
I wake up at 2am
In tears
Worried
For the America I love
But
Can't feel her anymore

Replying to @HellBentVet Not really a poem
Just desperation
Burning from my soul
I don't want the America he is making great
It's one I too can't breathe in
